From 79576bd75590dc95ff1485563532e11b17021d08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Arnaldi <michael.arnaldi@effectful.co>
Date: Fri, 24 Jul 2026 13:44:19 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] api: add getExpressionTypeAtPosition

getTypeAtPosition resolves the innermost node at a position, which for
the start of foo.bar(baz) is the identifier foo. API consumers asking
about an expression (e.g. editors augmenting hover for language
constructs that compile to plain expressions) want the type of the
whole expression instead.

getExpressionTypeAtPosition ascends from the touching node through
enclosing expressions that share its start position, stopping below
yield expressions so the operand of yield* is answered with its own
type rather than the unwrapped yielded-value type.

For content-mapped files the incoming position is interpreted in the
file's original text and mapped forward through the span map
(PurposeSemantic), matching how LSP position-based features treat
mapped files; getTypeAtPosition continues to operate in transformed
coordinates.
